    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Order containing around 370 species in three families of shrews, moles, and kin. Moles (family Talpidae) are sometimes classified with hedgehogs in Erinaceomorpha. It is now often classified as a biological clade within the class of mammals, because members apparently are paraphyletic (i.e., a taxonomic group which does not include all the descendants of an ancestral taxon).</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
